This paper deals with physical human-robot interaction, which is a topic that falls under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The paper also discusses the control strategy for the robot, which falls under the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category. The focus on minimizing the effort for the operator suggests that the paper may also belong to the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. The adaptation of the controller parameters is a machine learning (cs.MA) problem, and the use of passivity in the controller design suggests that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
